                <p>Notice that the mean is each number of goals per game multiplied by its relative
                    frequency. Since we usually write the relative frequencies as decimals, we can
                    see that: </p>
                <table rowstyle="plain">
                    <tr>
                        <td align="right">mean number of goals per game</td>
                        <td align="center">=</td>
                        <td align="left"> 0(.089) + 1(.234) + 2(.266) + 3(.193) + 4(.130) + 5(.057)
                            + 6(.016) + 7(.010) + 8(.005) </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td/>
                        <td align="center">=</td>
                        <td align="left">2.36, rounded to two decimal places</td>
                    </tr>
